headline: Smurfit Westrock touts ‘significant improvements’ to operations at 1-year mark
summary: The company will continue efforts to optimize its corrugated box system, including through adjusting its footprint and cutting “loss-making” customer contracts, executives said on a Wednesday earnings call.

headline: Smurfit Westrock: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: Smurfit Westrock Plc (SW) on Wednesday reported a loss of $28 million in its second quarter. On a per-share basis, the Dublin 4, Ireland-based company said it had a loss of 5 cents. Earnings, adjusted for asset impairment costs and restructuring costs, were 45 cents per share.
